|

SmartIT is a software development company with 10 years extensive experience
in programming business-orientated solutions. Our team of 30 programmers has
far-reaching enterprise-level practice on constructing ERP, CRM, CMS and
utility controls. The software systems of SmartIT help 6 500 associates in the
non-banking financial sector of Poland, Czech Republic, Ukraine, Romania,
Macedonia and Bulgaria, to serve 500 000 clients every day.  

Our team is growing and now we have a new opening for the position of **JUNIOR
DATA WAREHOUSE SPECIALIST**.  

**Job description:**  

• Develop and maintain existing and new data warehouse, and ETL processes;  
• Provide guidance and recommendation on the data warehouse architecture;  
• Produce and maintain high quality documentation for the project.  

**Requirements:**  

• Knowledge in Data Warehousing;  
• Familiar with Relational databases, dimensional and OLAP modeling;  
• Experience with ETL tools;  
• Experience with Microsoft Business Intelligence tools (SSRS, SSIS, SSAS) is
an advantage, but not required;  
• SQL programming skills (T-SQL or PL/SQL, stored procedures, functions,
views, etc.);  
• Professional experience with SQL is a great advantage;  
• Experience working within Financial Services Sector is an advantage, but not
required.

**Benefits:**  

• Plenty of opportunities for professional growth in our local or
international operations;  
• Interesting work on new and long-run projects;  
• Friendly working environment and strong corporate management;  
• Competitive salary based on personal and team achievements;  
• Smart mobile phone and sponsored mobile plan;  
• Company-sponsored training and certification;  
• Regular team buildings and celebrations.  

We are searching for candidates who enjoy working with people in a fast-paced,
growing environment. If you have a drive to succeed and advance your career,
SmartIT might be a fit for you.  

We encourage you to take a couple minutes to submit your resume to be
considered as the newest member to our professional team.  

We are an equal employment opportunity employer. Qualified applicants will
receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion,
sex, sexual orientation, gender perception or identity, national origin, age,
marital status or disability status.

|  Основни задължения и отговорности:  

• Оказва съдействие при разрешаването на въпроси, свързани с използването на
предлаганите от фирмата софтуерни продукти;  
• Извършва дейности по инсталация и конфигуриране на специализиран софтуер при
клиента или отдалечено през интернет;  
• Участва активно в процеса по внедряване на софтуерните приложения и извършва
обучение на персонала на клиента;  
• Осъществява комуникация с клиенти по телефон, skype и електронна поща;  
• Води база данни с входящи запитвания и досие на клиентите;  
• Осъществява анализ на клиентските изисквания;  
• Активно комуникира с техническия и търговския отдел във фирмата и
осъществява обратна връзка с клиента;  

Изисквания:  

• Умения за работа в екип;  
• Отлични комуникативни умения и положителна нагласа към хората;  
• Клиенто-ориентиран подход и начин на поведение;  
• Отлична компютърна грамотност – MS Office, Internet, Компютърни мрежи;  
• Висше техническо или икономическо образование е предимство;  
• Предишен опит на същата или подобна позиция ще се счита за предимство;  
• Валидна шофьорска книжка е предимство;  
• Владеене на английски език е предимство;  

Ние предлагаме:  
• Адекватно заплащане;  
• Динамична и интересна работа в приятен и сплотен екип от професионалисти;  
• Коректно отношение и нормална работна обстановка;

|  EGT Interactive is an industry-leading provider of online gambling software
and solutions and powers one of the most successful gaming operators in the
World. The company is entirely IT –oriented, so you will be working for a team
that highly prizes technology and enthusiasm. Opportunities are only limited
by your ability, motivation and imagination, we simply believe in hiring the
best people for the expanding interactive gaming market.  


EGT Interactive wants to expand aggressively so is looking to hire passionate
and talented software developers.  

**If you:**  
-think logically;  
-are self-driven;  
-are motivated and dedicated to the software craft;  
-like challenging tasks;  
-want to improve and learn a lot of new cool technologies;  
-work with cutting edge frameworks;  
-have good understanding of Java/C++/C# or any other object oriented language;  
-have knowledge of SQL and relational databases;  

…apply by sending your CV!  

**A great plus will be:**  
-real work experience;  
-knowledge of Java EE.  

**We can offer:**  
-friendly work environment;  
-great remuneration package and regular promotions for proven achievements;  
-social package;  
-flexible working hours;  
-challenging and dynamic work;  
-opportunities for personal and career development.  

Office Location: 135-A, Tsarigrasko Shose Blvd, Floor 7  
Mobile: +359 882 111 943  

_ All applications will be considered under the terms and conditions of
confidentiality in accordance with the regulations of personal data
protection._

|  THE EXPERIENCE MATTERS  

C3i Healthcare Connections, a division of Telerex is an American company,
leading provider of technical support services for life sciences companies
worldwide. We operate in the field of Information technologies (IT) and their
application for the needs of the Pharmaceutical industry and clinical research
organizations. Since we had opened the office in Sofia, Bulgaria in 2005, we
managed to attract many talented and motivated people and helped them develop
their potential.  

To ensure the expansion of our Operations Centre in Sofia, Bulgaria we are now
looking to recruit a CRM Administrator.  

The CRM Administrator is an expert in various CRM systems and applications and
is responsible for providing Tier II support to clients. Resolving requests
and system/applications administration is the main focus of the role.  


Main responsibilities:  

• Perform ticket creation, categorization, assignment and follow-up
distribution. Communicate issues to the Client and the management;  
• Monitor batch jobs, perform troubleshooting of incidents and fulfill
requests;  
• Independently resolve issues within the area of expertise or escalate to the
appropriate level of competence;  
• Proactively investigate recurring issues and develop knowledge articles in
the knowledge base;  
• Support testing of enhancements or changes of existing systems and
applications;  
• Implement system changes and configurations;  
• Follow-up on the Tier II team’s pending activities, open requests and
incidents and help drive them toward resolution;  
• Resolve complex Tier II technical issues;  
• Assist the Tier II team on internally escalated cases;  
• Collaborate with the Tier II team and engage Sr. CRM Administrator to
resolve issues and find improvement opportunities and create value for the
Client and C3i;  
• Perform quality check of the Tier II team’s production work;  
• Train new hires, share knowledge and experience with peers to constantly
increase capabilities of the Tier II team;  


Job requirements:  

• Strong understanding of CRM and related technologies: SQL, SFDC, VEEVA,
Informatica, Database administration, HTML Coding, QlikView, Active Directory,
Microsoft Exchange, Microsoft SCCM;  
• Cooperativeness and team work orientation;  
• Process orientation, capability to analyze and improve processes;  
• Very good judgment and decision making;  
• Customer Service Orientation;  
• Excellent verbal and written communication skills in English;  


Education:  

• Bachelor degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or similar
discipline, or equivalent experience;  
• VEEVA/ SalesForce.com certification required;  
• MCSA certification preferred;  
• MCSE or Oracle certification preferred.  


Experience:  

• 2 years of experience in systems and applications administration preferred;  
• 1 year of experience in Quality assurance and Quality check of Tier II
support preferred;  
• 2 years of experience with Active Directory / Microsoft Exchange preferred;  
• Support center environment experience preferred;  


What we offer:  

• Professional on-boarding and on-going trainings  
• Real opportunities for career progression with leading US Company  
• Competitive salary and performance bonuses  
• Social benefits package  
• Vibrant environment  

Are you willing to build up your career with us? - We’ll be happy to receive
your resume in English!  

*Your personal data is secure with us.  
** Only candidates selected for interview will be contacted

|

Object Systems International (OSI) is a leading provider of Enterprise Cloud
and Mobile systems. Since 1998, the company's products have been used to
manage business-critical data for small businesses and Fortune 100 clients
alike. OSI’s technology serves tens of thousands of users in travel,
government, healthcare, and other markets. OSI is headquartered in the United
States, with a development center located in Sofia, Bulgaria.

We are expanding our business, adding about 50 people over the next few
months. We are looking for a talented **Lead QA Engineer** to drive the
functional and automation testing in the team. The right person will have a
strong combination of technical and collaboration skills.

**Responsibilities:**

  * Setup and improve the QA processes in the agile teams;
  * Develop, maintain and extend the automated and manual software test suites;
  * Report on product quality metrics;
  * Train, mentor and coach team members;
  * Drive testability requirements into the product;
  * Participate in hiring a team of 7-10 people;
  * Facilitate design and test reviews;
  * Work with the team scrum master to monitor project velocities and help maintain a smooth process;
  * Participate in the performance review process.

**Requirements:**

  * 2+ years of experience leading the QA processes in agile teams;
  * 6+ years of experience in **Software Development as QA Test Automation Engineer or Developer;**
  * Strong understanding of Software Development, including requirements definition through production;
  * Experienced with different types of Test Management, Bug Tracking and Test Automation tools;
  * Excellent written and verbal communication skills;
  * Good English;
  * Some travel to US may be required.

**Nice to have (pluses):**

  * Experience using Selenium;
  * Experience with Behavior Driven Development (BDD) - SpecFlow or Cucumber;
  * Experience in Test Driven Development;
  * Previous experience in DevOps environments;
  * Experience working in agile environments, especially Scrum;
  * Good understanding of programming – OOP, cycles, recursion, data structures, algorithms;
  * Previous test automation experience (single page web applications and web services);
  * Experience working with Microsoft stack of development technologies: Visual Studio, TFS and extensions;
  * Experience testing applications on AWS or Azure.

**OSI offers:**

  * A competitive salary and social benefits;
  * Friendly work environment and nice attitude;
  * Work-life balance;
  * Modern and comfortable office close to the metro station "Opalchenska", Mall Sofia;
  * Opportunities for career development in an international company.

_If you are interested in this opportunity, please send your CV in English.  
All applications will be treated as strictly confidential.  
Only short-listed candidates will be contacted._

